<HEADLINE> Stampede Claims 5 in Nigerian Stadium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Five persons were feared dead and
dozens of others were injured during a stampede at the Lagos
National Stadium of Nigeria on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Local media reports said today that the stampede was caused by
policemen who were trying to block one of the gates to outing
fans to allow dignitaries watching the World Cup qualifier
between Nigeria and Guinea to go first.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy occurred when fans behind kept pressing forward to
the gate, thus injuring those at the front, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Reports also pointed out that the tragedy might be avoided if
all the five gates of the stadium were opened. Instead, reports
said only two gates were in use at the time of the incident.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria beat Guinea 2-1 in that match to top Group A in the
African region in the '98 French World Cup qualifying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
