<HEADLINE> Joaquim Chissano Meets SADC Parliament Speakers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano received Saturday parliament speakers from the member
states of the Southern African Development Community (SADC) who
had arrived here in Maputo to take part in the SADC Parliament
Forum.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Noticias reported today that president
Chissano during the meeting expressed his satisfaction with the
establishment of the Forum, saying that this Forum will further
promote the relations of the various southern African
countries.
</P>
<P>
The development of southern Africa requires further regional
cooperation, the president said.
</P>
<P>
With regard to regional laws, the president said that the
laws were inherited from the colonial period and therefore
should be rectified according to "our own experience".
</P>
<P>
The two-day Forum meeting ended Saturday, said Vice-speaker
Abdul Kanimo of the Assembly of the Republic of Mozambique,
adding that the meeting decided that the first Plenary Session of
the Forum be convened in Cape Town on July 31.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, apart from Malawi, Parliament
speakers from Mozambique, South Africa, Angola, Zimbabwe,
Mauritius, Zambia, Lesotho, Tanzania, Botswana, Swaziland and
Namibia attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
