<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Repair Border Railings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique will rebuild its 350-
kilometer-long railings along its borders with South Africa and
Swaziland, the Mozambique Information Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, this has been revealed by Mozambican
Minister of Internal Affairs Almerino Manheje, who recently
inspected the Mozambique-South Africa and Mozambique-Swaziland
borders.
</P>
<P>
He added that his ministry will join the Ministry of Finance
and Planning to adopt concrete measures to rebuild the
border railings.
</P>
<P>
Manheje noted that the border railings have long been out of
repair, thus providing opportunities to illegal trade, drug and
weapons trafficking and other criminal activities.
</P>
<P>
The situation cannot be allowed any longer and must be
reversed as soon as possible, he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
