<HEADLINE> African Laboratory Scientists to Meet in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Africa's top laboratory
scientists are due to meet in Harare for the Fifth Congress of
the Association of Medical Laboratory Scientists of Central and
Southern Africa on April 13-16.
</P>
<P>
One of the organizers of the congress Akim Abayomi said here
today, "official invitations have been extended to every ministry
of health in Africa to send representatives."
</P>
<P>
Abayomi said, "the intention is to provide a platform for the
congregation of high calibre scientists from throughout Africa to
recognize one another and exchange ideas about existing
activities in their respective countries."
</P>
<P>
He added that they hoped to resolve the major medical issues
affecting the continent, and initiate a unification process with
the specific purpose of encouraging collaborative exchange
between the regions.
</P>
<P>
High on the list of topics will be the development of
appropriate technologies against the scourges of tuberculosis and
HIV virus which causes AIDS, as well as the formation of an all
Africa laboratory scientists association, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
