<HEADLINE> Sudanese Peace Council Hopes to End War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the
Sudanese Peace Council Mohamed al Amin Khalifa today expressed the
hope that a peace agreement scheduled to be signed soon will put
an end to the ongoing war that is squandering Sudan's potentials
and capabilities.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the press, Khalifa described the peace
agreement as closing the page of fighting, destruction and
devastation, and opening a new page of construction and
development in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
Khalifa said that an end to the ongoing war in south and east
Sudan would usher in the beginning of the long-cherished
development that would lead the Sudan to stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
As a matter of fact, a peace agreement has been concluded
between the Sudanese government and the rebel groups that wanted
to break away from the Sudan and establish a separatist state. The
formal signing ceremony is due to take place within a few days.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary General of the Sudanese Peace Council further
disclosed that consultations were under way between the Sudanese
government and the rebel factions to define the date and venue for
the signing of the agreement. He expressed his hope that all
factions of the rebel movement would opt for peace and join the
agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
