<HEADLINE> U.S. Vice President to Visit Egypt in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 6 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Vice President Al Gore will
start a visit to Egypt next month to push ahead the Egyptian-U.S.
partnership, an Egyptian official announced today.
</P>
<P>
Gore will chair the Egyptian-American Presidents' Council
meetings during his several days' stay here, Shafik Gabr, a senior
member of the Council's Executive Committee was quoted by MENA,
the Egyptian news agency.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the Council meetings will continue talks
on the partnership process held during the five-day visit by
President Hosni Mubarak last month to the U.S., the largest donor
country to Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The official expressed the hope that the meeting will open new
vistas for U.S. investment in Egypt, which accounted for 3.5
percent of the total foreign investments in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
A proposal for signing an agreement on free trade between the
two countries will also be discussed, he said.
</P>
<P>
Volume of trade between the two countries reached 3.713 billion
dollars last year as exports to the U.S. markets amounted to 713
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
U.S. investments in Egypt have reached around 2 billion
dollars and they are concentrated on the petroleum field.
</P>
<P>
There are U.S. investment in 191 companies in Egypt and the
U.S. participation in productive projects reached 25 percent of
its total investment here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
