<HEADLINE> Syrian Vice-President's China Visit Important: Ambassador Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The upcoming visit by Syrian
Vice-President Abdel Halim Khaddam to China is an important one,
coming at a crucial time in the Middle East peace process, Syrian
Ambassador to China Loutof Allah Haydar said in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Haydar told Xinhua that the current situation in the Middle
East is "subtle" and "dangerous" and may badly destroy the peace
process.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian vice-president is scheduled to visit China on April
9, and is expected to meet with Chinese leaders to discuss ways of
re-starting the stalled peace process and what China can do.
</P>
<P>
Peace is a strategic choice of Syria and should be based on the
return of Israeli-occupied Arab land and the recovery of the
rights of the Arab people, he said, emphasizing that "security" is
essential to both negotiating parties.
</P>
<P>
Syria is willing to resume negotiations with Israel on the basis
of the common understanding on "troop withdrawal" and "security
arrangements" reached by Syria and the former Israeli government,
instead of starting all over again, he said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he pointed out that Syria strongly opposes
the activities of Israeli authorities in building Jewish
settlements in Har Homa in east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
China, as an old friend of Syria, has always supported the just
cause of the Arab people, the ambassador said, adding that China's
stand on the Middle East issue is clear and widely welcomed by
Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that Syria hopes to develop Syrian-Chinese friendship
and cooperation into a "good example in international relations"
and that China, as a permanent member of the UN Security Council,
will play an even greater role in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
</TEXT>
