<HEADLINE> Japanese Business Group Visits Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Acting Mayor of Chongqing, Pu
Haiqing, met a 54-member delegation of Kansai business people,
headed by Tetsuro Kawakami, chairman of the Kansai Economic
Federation, today in this southwestern Chinese city.
</P>
<P>
Pu told the visitors that Chongqing has recently been given
municipality status, under the direct control of the central
government, bringing more opportunities for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing is improving its investment environment and opening
wider to the outside world, he said, and that many Japanese
industrial giants have been cooperating with local firms in
Chongqing and that two Japanese banks have offices in the city.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the city is ready to cooperate further
with Japanese companies.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Kawakami said that Kansai business people
want to maintain close ties with Chongqing and that eight firms
have been set up in the Chinese city backed by Kansai-based
companies, and Kansai International Airport will open a direct
flight to Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese business people have been visiting China since
April 2. Chongqing is on the second leg of their tour, after
Beijing. They are scheduled to leave for Shanghai on Tuesday and
will end their China visit on April 10. 
</P>
