<HEADLINE> 22 Injuried in Train Derailment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 22 people were injured,
four of them seriously, when a four-car local train derailed this
afternoon southwest of Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Kyodo reported that the accident happened in Yokosuka, Kanagawa
Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Three of the four cars went off the tracks around 2:45
p.m. local time (0545 GMT) after the train, carrying about 60
passengers, ran onto landslide earth on the tracks. Train services
were temporarily halted because of the accident.
</P>
<P>
About 300 cubic meters of earth and sand fell onto the tracks
after several days of rain loosened soil on a hill near the
tracks, the railway company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
