<HEADLINE> 2 French Mirage 2000 Crash Into Sea, Pilots Survive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Mirage 2000 N of the French Air
Force crashed into the Mediterranean Sea at noon today, but all
the four members of their crews survived, the Agence France-Presse
quoted an air force source as saying.
</P>
<P>
The two fighters, from the 3/4 "Limousin" chaser squadron of
the 125 air base in Isere near Marseille, were on a training
mission without carrying weapons when they crashed.
