<HEADLINE> Rosset Moves into Second Round at Hong Kong Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Marc Rosset advanced
to the second round of the Salem Hong Kong Open after scoring a
6-2, 6-2 victory over unseeded German Nicolas Kiefer here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The world number 18 Swiss player wrapped up the match in only
54 minutes to book a second-round clash with either wild card
entry Carl Chang or qualifier Brian MacPhie.
</P>
<P>
Rosset defeated Kiefer in three sets on his way to winning
February's European Community Championships in Antwerp
</P>
<P>
Eighth-seeded Czech Danial Vacek also entered the second round,
defeating Russian Alexander Volkov 6-4, 7-6 (7-3) in his
first-round match.
</P>
<P>
Swede Henrik Holm, recently back from a lengthy absence due to
a shoulder injury, squandered three match points in going down
6-1, 6-7 (1-7), 2-6 to American Justin Gimelstob.
</P>
<P>
World number three and top seed Michael Chang opens his
campaign for a third Hong Kong title Tuesday against local wild
card entry Melvin Tong.
</P>
<P>
Chang took over the top seeding here following the withdrawal
of world number one and defending champion Pete Sampras who pulled
out on Thursday with a wrist injury. 
</P>
