<HEADLINE> Most French Troops to Be Deployed in Albania to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Most of the 850 French soldiers to
be deployed on the ground in Albania as part of the multinational
protection force will be from the 9th Division of the Infantry of
the French Navy.
</P>
<P>
The Agence France-Presse quoted military sources as saying
today that the 2nd Regiment of the Infantry of the Navy will send
500 men to Albania, while the Regiment of the Infantry and Tank of
the Navy will send a squadron of armored vehicles with about 130
men.
</P>
<P>
A reconnaissance unit of the French Navy and 150 other French
soldiers to serve in the office of the chief of staff of the
multinational force and a military helicopter squadron will also
be sent to Albania.
</P>
<P>
All the French soldiers will be placed under the command of
Colonel Philippe Roisin, chief of the 2nd Corps of the Regiment of
the Infantry of Navy, together with 150 other French military men
who will make up the rest of the 1,000-man French contingent in
Albania.
</P>
<P>
The 850 French soldiers will leave the southern French port of
Toulon Thursday for the port city Durres in northern Albania.
</P>
<P>
A French Defense Ministry spokesman said last week that French
troops will be deployed between Durres and Tirana to secure the
arrival and sending of humanitarian goods to the Albanians.
</P>
<P>
Some European countries have suggested that a multinational
task force be sent to southern Albania, where tension remains high
after anti-government riots broke out in early March.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6,000 soldiers from Italy, France, Greece, Turkey,
Austria, Romania and Denmark will join the multinational force
proposed by the Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe and approved by the United Nations Security Council.
</P>
</TEXT>
