<HEADLINE> Algeria Creates 1st Free Economic, Trade Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Algerian Prime Minister Ahmed
Ouvahia signed a decree last Saturday on the creation of the
country's first free economic and trade zone in Bellara, in the
department of Jijel 300 kilometers east of the capital Algiers.
</P>
<P>
Algerian newspapers said that the locality of the zone was
chosen by the National Agency of Territorial Management among 15
candidates, because of its proximity to the port of Djendjen and
the existence of a local electricity power center with 630
megawatts of power.
</P>
<P>
Bellara is also close to an airport and has highway and railway
links with all the major cities in the eastern part of the
country.
</P>
<P>
It is also one hour's flight from such Mediterranean
metropolises as Marseille, Naples and Barcelona. 
</P>
