<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Business Executives Take Courses in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Executives from Hong Kong's Swire
Group today started to take a week-long course on "Contemporary
China Study" in Beijing-based Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Qinghua University said that this is the 41st
class on the same subject for senior management personnel in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, Qinghua has sponsored a series of China study
seminars for senior civil servants in Hong Kong. Because of this,
business and financial people in Hong Kong asked the university to
open courses catering to their needs.
</P>
<P>
By the end of March, the university had organized 40 classes
for executives from Hong Kong companies like Swire Group, Hong
Kong Telecom, Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corporation, and the
Sun Hung Kai Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Those taking the course hear lectures by local experts or
government officials on such topics as the Basic Law of Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, China's current economic situation,
state enterprise reforms, and the legal and financial systems of
China. 
