<HEADLINE> 17 Hurt in Road Mishap in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A woman on her way to market died
while 17 others were injured today when a cargo truck they rode
rammed into another truck in Sibonga town in the central
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The women, who was going to the market to sell her vegetables,
died instantly due to serious head and body injuries from the
accident, local police said.
</P>
<P>
All the injured had been sent to hospital, police said, adding
that two of them are now in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation said the accident occurred because the
driver of the ill-fated truck was not able to see the other dump
truck loaded with coal on the roadside.
</P>
<P>
Police is now conducting a thorough investigation on the
accident.
</P>
</TEXT>
