<HEADLINE> China Designates 1997 "Year of Agronomy" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China will launch a year-long
nationwide campaign to popularize agricultural science and
technology to make certain that grain harvests are good.
</P>
<P>
More scientific achievements are expected to be applied in
production, said Bai Zhijian, vice minister of Agriculture, at a
press conference in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The Agriculture Ministry will promote this year the
popularization of ten techniques that include dry farming,
sparse-planting and seed-spraying methods, a unified supply of
wheat strains, and corn cultivation under plastic sheets.
</P>
<P>
Bai urged all provinces and autonomous regions to build
agronomy centers at the county, township, and village levels in at
least a third of the rural counties by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The country will send 900,000 technicians, including 180,000
agronomists, down to rural areas to offer technical guidance, and
agricultural research institutes and agronomy centers are being
urged to teach farmers one or two practical skills by holding
training courses.
</P>
<P>
Bai said that 70 percent of spending on capital construction of
the state budget this year will be in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Science and technology played a decisive role in 1996's grain
harvest, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
