cooperation which would lead to facilitation of trade within the
organization.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the inaugural session of two-day first meeting of
the SAARC (South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation)
countries on customs cooperation, Aziz said the conference had to
decide a number of initiatives and the results of this conference
would be watched carefully as they could usher in a new era for
traders in the region.
</P>
<P>
"As we approach the 21st century, the role of customs has to be
changed," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the overall progress which SAARC achieved in
promoting economic cooperation is less than expected because of
political problems between member countries but at sectoral and
technical level, very useful interaction has been taking place.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan is fully aware of the importance of international
trade, he said.
</P>
<P>
With this objective in mind, Pakistan recently introduced major
tax reforms through the industrial revival package, he said.
</P>
<P>
Through this bold move, he said "we have reduced the maximum
customs tariff from 65 percent to 45 percent. The tariff slabs
have been reduced from 13 to 5 and special concessionary rates
will be reduced to the maximum possible degree."
</P>
<P>
All this is aimed at simplifying customs tariff and to make it
more transparent, he said adding the reduced tariff, besides
reviving industry, would lead to increased international trade, he
added.  
</P>
