The Lao official news agency, KPL, reported today that an
agreement was reached last week in the Thai capital of Bangkok, on
jointly curbing and cracking down on various border crimes.
</P>
<P>
These included smuggling of illegal goods and military weapons,
the illicit extraction of natural resources, and trafficking of
women for prostitution and labor.
</P>
<P>
The agreement called for close exchange of information and
data, and jointly preventing damage to the natural environment in
border areas before demarcation was completed.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also agreed to facilitate immigration and
make cross visits easier. They agreed to inform each other of
arrests made in their territories and allow visits by diplomatic
officials or relatives of the arrested.
</P>
<P>
They will cooperate closely in fighting drug crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
