<HEADLINE> Chinese Central Bank to Expand Think-Tank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC),
the central bank, is moving to reinforce its research departments,
expand its nationwide information networks, and get access to the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
The moves are aimed at meeting the demands of the
fast-developing banking industry and financial reforms in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Some local observers said that the central bank is attaching
greater importance to the research work and international
information of the banking sector.
</P>
<P>
Since the late 1970s, when China adopted reform and opening
policies, PBOC has played an increasingly bigger role in the
development of the national economy and the government's
policy-making.
</P>
<P>
The role of the central bank became even more important during
the 1993-96 period, when the government succeeded in carrying out
its macro-economic control, and cooled down the over-heated
economy.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the central bank are so proud of PBOC's role in
that period that they boast of frequent visits to Zhongnanhai,
where the Central Committee of the ruling Communist Party of China
(CPC), the State Council, and the cabinet, are located.
</P>
<P>
PBOC researchers are often called in to Zhongnanhai, when the
government ponders over making decisions on some key economic and
financial issues, they said.
</P>
<P>
They said that to reinforce the think-tank and make full use of
theorists are of great significance for democratic and scientific
decision-making in the government regarding financial matters.
</P>
<P>
According to PBOC sources, the leadership of the central bank
is now planning to implement an overall reinforcement of the
research and information departments.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yaoxian, vice-governor of the central bank who is
responsible for the research and information sectors, said at a
recent PBOC meeting that the central bank will strengthen the
research bodies in the headquarters and major local branches.
</P>
<P>
The research institutions will cooperate and study certain key
problems arising from the current situation, he said, stressing
that the achievements of the studies should be applied to the
practical work.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, he said, the central bank plans to, within
the next two or three years, build up nationwide data links and
get access to Internet.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, of the over 1,000 universities
and colleges in China, some 400 have opened financial departments
or sections, which have become a major source of talent for the
country's banking industry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, many Chinese studying overseas, who majored in
financial subjects, have returned to the motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
