<HEADLINE> Albania Allows EU Mission to Expand Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Albania decided Sunday to allow a
European Union (EU) mission to expand its activities from the
border area to the whole country, reported Albanian Telegraphic
Agency today.
</P>
<P>
Albania made the decision in an effort to restore order that
had been disrupted by a nationwide unrest triggered by a
pyramid-investment scheme since January.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made under a national reconciliation agreement
reached on March 9 by President Sali Berisha and ten main parties
calling for foreign military assistance.
</P>
<P>
The EU mission, composed of diplomats and soldiers, entered
Albania in 1992 under the request of the Albanian government to
monitor the situation along its borders with the republics of the
former Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a U.N-authorized multinational protection force led
by Italy will start to arrive by April 14 in Albania to help end
the crisis. 
</P>
