<HEADLINE> Bomb Kills Myanmar Leader's Daughter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded on Sunday night
here at the residence of the Second Secretary of the State Law and
Order Restoration Council of Myanmar Lieutenant-General Tin Oo,
killing the General's eldest daughter, Myanmar authorities
confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
An initial investigation said that it was a parcel bomb.
</P>
<P>
It was the second bomb attack in Myanmar's capital in less than
four months after the one which went off last December at the Maha
Pasana Cave of the Kaba Aye Pagoda where a Chinese Buddha's tooth
relic was kept for public worship, killing five people and
injuring 17 others.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, raids on some Moslem mosques in Yangon by some
Buddhist monks also took place in March. The religious unrest was
spread from Mandalay, Myanmar's second largest city, where a
dusk-to-dawn curfew has been in force since March 17.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar authorities said in an earlier statement, which is not
made public, that the situation in Mandalay and Yangon have been
under control.  
</P>
