<HEADLINE> Arafat Calls for NAM Support in Restoring Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Yasser Arafat, president of the
Palestinian National Authority, today appealed to the Non-aligned
Movement (NAM) countries to help restore the Middle East peace
process to its tracks.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a special session of the 12th NAM ministerial
meeting which opened here today, Arafat said that the decision of
the Israeli government to build a new settlement at Jabal Abu
Ghaniem in East Jerusalem and other Palestinian locations
constitutes a "flagrant violation to the international will and to
resolutions of international legitimacy."
</P>
<P>
Arafat said "the Israeli aggressive measures and acts, its
tight security measures and the military mobilization imposed on
the Palestinian lands are equal to a declaration of war not only
on the Palestinian people, but also on the peace process and on
all those who believe in peace and do care for its progress and
success in the region."
</P>
<P>
In this context, the economic blockades and collective
punishment imposed on the Palestinian people not only contradict
the texts and principles of the peace process but also represent a
catastrophe for the infant Palestinian economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said altering the situation in Jerusalem through
confiscation, excavations, demolishing and building settlements is
a violation of Israel's commitment of what it had signed in Oslo.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli settlement activities in Jabal Abu Ghneim in East
Jerusalem are null and void, Arafat said.
</P>
<P>
"Jerusalem is the core of the Palestinian cause, it is the key
of peace and war in the region," he stated, adding that "peace
will not be realized unless Jerusalem returns to its legitimate
owners as the capital of the Independent Palestinian state."
</P>
<P>
Arafat noted that "no peace can be realized with settlement,
which swallow the Palestinian and Arab land and change it to
cantons isolated from each other."
</P>
<P>
President Arafat appealed to NAM countries to help save the
peace process from this impasse that the current Israeli
government pushed to by providing political, financial and moral
support for the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
The two-day 12th Ministerial Conference of NAM countries, which
opened here this morning, was attended by foreign ministers from
over 70 countries.
</P>
<P>
Both United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan and Indian
Prime Minister H.D. Deve Gowda addressed the inaugural session.
</P>
</TEXT>
