<HEADLINE> India Sitting on AIDS Bomb: IHO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- India will have 20 to 50 million
HIV infected persons by the turn of the century, the Indian Health
Organization (IHO) sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The dreaded HIV virus, initially infecting the sex workers in
the country, has now reached its third phase as it has been
detected among housewives and children signaling a major crisis on
hand.
</P>
<P>
IHO shelved all its other activities in 1989 to dedicate
services fully towards controlling of the HIV menace.
</P>
<P>
It claimed that about 300,000 people were saved from HIV
infections through various programs of the IHO, which was the
first in the country to launch mobile AIDS clinics, AIDS hotline,
anonymous HIV Testing Centers and counseling centers.  
</P>
