<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Unit Trust Net Sales Soared in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The unit trust Net sales soared
to new highs, reaching 266.41 million US dollars, up by 58.3
percent over January though gross sales dipped by 4.3 percent,
according to the Hong Kong Investment Funds Association (HKIFA).
</P>
<P>
Andrew Lo, chairman of the HKIFA, said that while January's
inflows were primarily dominated by a single sector -- Hong Kong
equity funds which accounted for 81.8 percent of the industry's
net inflows, February's net sales were attributed to high inflows
into a number of sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said that the key contributor was Single Asian countries
funds, which cover various types of single Asian country funds
which accounted for 81.8 percent of the industry's net inflows.
</P>
<P>
The second leading sector was bond funds, which took up 21.1
percent, he added.
</P>
<P>
Gross sales of Hong Kong equity funds in February dropped by
56.9 percent over January and net sales dropped by 87.7 percent to
16.87 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The HKIFA consists of 45 fund companies as full members, and 34
professional firms, which include trustees, accountants and
lawyers as associate members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
