<HEADLINE> Chinese, French Defense Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China is willing to work with
France to further the long-term and stable friendship and
cooperation between the armed forces of the two countries, said
Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian.
</P>
<P>
During the talks with visiting French Defense Minister Charles
Millon here this morning, Chi hailed the great importance of
Millon's visit to China, which is the first by a French defense
minister since China and France established diplomatic relations
in 1964.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also vice-chairman of China's Central Military
Commission and state councillor, said the relationship between the
two armed forces is an important part of the Sino-French ties.
With the restoration and development of the bilateral ties in the
past few years, he added, the friendly cooperation between the two
armed forces has entered a new phase.
</P>
<P>
Chi said he believes the current visit of the French defense
minister will make a great contribution to the development of the
relations between the two countries and the two armed forces, and
will push the bilateral cooperation to a new high.
</P>
<P>
Chi briefed the French visitor on China's defense policy, army
building and the achievements in the country's reforms and opening
up program.
</P>
<P>
The "China threat" theory spread by some people in the world,
Chi said, aims at sowing discord between China and its neighboring
countries and obstructing China's growth.
</P>
<P>
Millon said he was happy to be the first defense minister of
his country visiting China. He introduced France's defense and
security policies, and put forward proposals on the development of
military exchanges and friendly cooperation between France and
China.
</P>
<P>
The two defense ministers also exchanged views on international
issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Chi presided over a welcome ceremony in
honor of Millon, who arrived Sunday on an official visit at the
invitation of Chi.
</P>
<P>
Millon met with Chinese Minister of Electronics Industry Hu
Qili and Chief of the General Staff of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army, Fu Quanyou, this morning and at noon
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
