<HEADLINE> Police Tighten Security in Colombo for New Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's police will tighten
security in the capital city of Colombo and its environs from this
evening in view of the forthcoming Sinhalese and Tamil New Year
which falls on April 12, according to police sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that policemen are being drawn from outstations
to man all key installations in the city.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of policemen including those from police training
schools have been already deployed in this exercise. Special
instructions have been given to them on how to tackle any
contingency during the course of their duties, the sources quoted
Deputy Inspector General of Colombo police T. B. Dissanayake as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The sources noted that with only a few days more for the New
Year, thousands of people are coming to the city to do their
shopping. Police will keep a strict check on the pickpockets,
especially during the festival times, they said.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that mobile police patrols will keep strict
vigilance along the city roads during the period.
</P>
<P>
A combined Sri Lankan security forces operation in several
areas of Colombo last Thursday resulted in the arrest of at least
300 Tamil rebel suspects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
