<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on the
Singapore market, while the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index increased 12.36 points to close at 2,088.14 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 107.03 million units, valued
at 274.52 million Singapore dollars (about 190.64 million US
dollars). Declines led advances by 163 to 151, while 290 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 4.29 million units. It was followed by
MBF Land which had 3.34 million shares traded. MBF Holdings was
next with 3.06 million shares changed hands.
</P>
