Singapore dollars to finish at 18.4 Singapore dollars. The
Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign increased by 50 cents
to end at 18.6 Singapore dollars, while the City Developments
Warrant 98 and the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC)
Foreign gained 30 cents each to close at 10.7 and 18.2 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Malaya Banking 200 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.2 dollars to end at 15 Singapore dollars. CDL Hotel
Ltd was next, falling by 45 cents to close at 3.8 Singapore
dollars, while MISC Foreign dropped by 26 cents to finish at 3.28
dollars.  
