<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Golden Jubilee Art Festival Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Grand Golden Jubilee Art
Festival began here today in celebration of the 50th anniversary
of Pakistan's independence.
</P>
<P>
The festival, with a theme of "Historical linkage with Central
Asia" has attracted 17 countries including China, Sri Lanka,
Malaysia, Egypt, Turkey and Central Asian Countries.
</P>
<P>
The festival, which will last until April 16, is being
organized by the National Golden Jubilee Committee. The 10-day
event will comprise celebrating Pakistan's historical and cultural
roots in Central Asia.
</P>
<P>
Artists and art ensembles from seven participating countries
will give their performances, while master craftsmen from more
than a dozen countries will display their works in the festival.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's all four provinces will exhibit their excellence in
colorful provincial pavilions based on the architecture of their
regions.
</P>
<P>
Song and dance ensembles will entertain visitors at different
places around the festival venue and at evening performances.
</P>
