<HEADLINE> Netherlands Helps Uganda Develop Northwestern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KMAPALA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands Development
organization has agreed to give an eight-million-U.S.-Dollar
grant for development projects in Uganda's northwestern districts
of Moyo, Arua and Nebbi.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here today, the agreement was
signed by A. Wehkamp, the director of the program in Uganda and
A. Awuzu, Ugandan State Minister for Local Government last week
in Arua town, northwestern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used to alleviate poverty through equitable
socio-economic development of people, fighting illiteracy and
training civic leaders in running project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
