<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Key Projects Start Construction in Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction of two key industrial
projects opened today in Haikou, capital of Hainan province in
south China.
</P>
<P>
One is to build a production line for cobalt oxide, with an
investment of 73 million yuan. The line is expected to produce 200
tons of cobalt oxide, 12 percent of the country's total, after
completion.
</P>
<P>
This project is likely to become the backbone of the province's
non-ferrous metal smelting industry, with an estimated output
value of 178 million yuan, said the local government.
</P>
<P>
The other project, with an investment of 15 million US dollars,
is to produce plasma substitutes.
</P>
<P>
Hainan province plans to begin building more than 100 key
projects this year to mark the decade since the founding of the
province.
</P>
<P>
All these projects, selected from the provincial plan for the
Ninth Five-Year-Plan period, are to be completed before April next
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
