<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Play More Important Role in Developing World Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China will play a more important
role in the world economy by its sound and rapid economic
development and the continuous access of its businesses to the
global market, according to an executive of the International
Chamber of Commerce (ICC).
</P>
<P>
Maria Livanos Cattaui, secretary general of the ICC, who is
here attending ICC 32nd World Congress, said today that ICC, as a
world non-governmental commercial organization, is devoted to
foring and enhancing close partnership among businesses in
China.
</P>
<P>
She said that ICC will help foreign enterprises and trade
communities become involved in the development China's market
economy and help China adapt itself to world trade.
</P>
<P>
Cattaui, who has visited China many times as an economic and
trade expert since the 1970s, noted that China's sponsorship of
the ICC 32nd World Congress with the theme of Asia in the Global
Economy reflects the remarkable achievement China has scored in
its economy, as well as the great interest of the international
business community in China.
</P>
<P>
ICC, set up in 1919, plays an important role in the
policy-making of the World Trade Organization (WTO) and is
influential in international economic and trade communities.
</P>
<P>
Cattaui said that she is confident that China will join the WTO
soon. Although China is yet to make improvements in some regards,
this will not prevent China from becoming a WTO member.
</P>
<P>
She noted that nothing can stop China from joining the WTO.
</P>
<P>
She said that ICC strongly supports China in jointing the WTO
and will work together with the Chinese government and enterprises
to this end. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
