<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
started the week in quiet trading today. It opened low in the
morning, but managed to recovered some points at the close.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 4 points lower at 2,221 with a turnover
of 25 million NZ dollars (17 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leaders, Air New Zealand and Carter Holt Harvey were
the only gainers. Air New Zealand shares climbed 3 cents to close
at 262 cents, and Carter Holt Harvey shares rose 1c to 307c.
</P>
<P>
Of the losers, Brierley Investment fell 2c to 128c, Fletcher
Building dropped 7c to 427c, Lion Nathan dipped 5c to 338c, and
Telecom fell 1c to 656c.  
