<HEADLINE> China World Trade Center to Issue Stocks in Hongkong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China World Trade Center Ltd., is
preparing to be listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange to fund its
expansion plans, sources disclosed here.
</P>
<P>
Located in the heart of Beijing's business and diplomatic
district, CTWC is a comprehensive enterprise featuring office,
exhibition, hotel, shopping and entertainment facilities, with a
total floor space of 430,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
A joint venture between China Foreign Economic and Trade
Consultance Co. under the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, and the Hong Kong-based Kerry Industrial Company
Ltd., CTWC turned over about 200 million US dollars in
1996. After-tax profits topped 84 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The company in March 1996 repaid the last batch of foreign
syndicate loans, three years and three months ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
In December, the company was approved by the State Council as
one of the fourth batch of enterprises to issue stocks overseas.
</P>
<P>
"The company is now developing in the direction of
conglomeration, diversification and internationalization," the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The company has begun a second phase of construction, putting
up another office building, more parking lots, and expanding the
shopping center. When completed in 1999, the total floor space
will be increased to 550,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The company, already engaged in real estate development, plans
to run a travel agency and buy equities in other
businesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
