<HEADLINE> More Beijing Residents Enjoy Low-Cost Apartments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 20,000 households in
Beijing are still living under crowded conditions and in the near
future, all of them will have much better living areas.
</P>
<P>
This year, the municipal government will start the construction
of 11 residential areas, according to Wang Zongli, director of the
Municipal Construction Commission. As a result, 11,000 households
are expected to move into more spacious rooms later this year.
</P>
<P>
Over the past four years, 31,000 households in Beijing have
benefited from the city government's program to construct low-cost
apartments.
</P>
<P>
The program, launched in 1993, is aimed at providing better
living conditions to the poor. Work units and local governments
are to guarantee that the apartments will be sold at cost.
</P>
<P>
With 1.1 billion yuan (132.5 million US dollars) in loans from
the World Bank, 25 low-cost residential projects with a total
floor space of 800,000 sq m will be launched this year, Wang
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
