<HEADLINE> Street Children Said National Problem in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Increasing street children in
Zimbabwe have become a national problem and the government should
have a common program to tackle it, the daily Herald said today.
</P>
<P>
The paper says the Harare city council recently strengthened
an exercise to send street children in the city to some
rehabilitation centers.
</P>
<P>
At first the well-coordinated exercise appeared to be
successful, but then was frustrated by a new influx of children
from other areas according to reports last week.
</P>
<P>
These children are aware that if they roamed the streets of
Harare, they would eventually be picked up and placed in a home,
said the paper.
</P>
<P>
The street children problem should be tackled nationally and
all local authorities should be involved and have a common
program and objective.
</P>
<P>
It is the time for the local authorities to set up a special
fund in their budgets to cater for the destitute children.
</P>
<P>
The paper said if there are joint efforts by all concerned,
the situation can be improved. 
</P>
