<HEADLINE> Diarrhea Claims 107 Lives in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harare, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Diarrhea has killed 107
Zimbabweans and afflicted another 58,209 countrywide in the past
three months, prompting the Health Ministry to increase its
educational campaigns against the disease.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ministry said Sunday in Bulawayo, the
second largest city, that the number of reported diarrhea cases
increase 13 percent since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
The increase was due to the incessant, heavy and widespread
rains in the just-ended season, he said.
</P>
<P>
The rains created unhygienic conditions in most urban areas,
resulting in an increased number of people being affected by
diarrhea. 
</P>
