<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Gives Zairean Refugees Asylum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe has so far this year
granted asylum to 10 refugees fleeing civil war in Zaire, the
dayly Herald reported today.
</P>
<P>
Commissioner for refugees Samuel Mhiribidi told the paper that
the country, which had until 1995 accommodated over 200,000
Mozambican refugees, has structures in place if there is need to
provide a safe haven for more Zaireans.
</P>
