<HEADLINE> Collections on Tibetan Folk Art Forms Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Two books of Tibetan folk art forms
have been published by the Tibet People's Publishing House,
believed to be the first such collection published in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
There are a dozen types of folk art forms in Tibet, handed down
from the long history of Tibetan arts and spread by clusters of
Tibetan artists, and they have become part of China's splendid
artistic treasure-house, said Tubdain, an old well-respected
actor-artist.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Tibetan artists have created a large number of
folk art works, many of which are popular among Tibetan farmers
and herdsmen, and at the same time have proved successful in
performances both at home and abroad, said Tubdain, who is also
vice-chairman of the Chinese Folk Arts Association.  
</P>
</TEXT>
