<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Move Manufacturing Plants To Outskirts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua)-- Shanghai plans to move its major
manufacturing plants and high-tech firms to its suburban areas,
while its downtown districts will mainly engage in financial and
commercial activities.
</P>
<P>
Owing to the rapid improvement of infrastructures and cheap
land and labor on the outskirts, new manufacturing centers will be
set up there. Each of the city's nine suburban counties and
districts has set up a development zone.
</P>
<P>
Each of the zones has its specific industrial development
targets. For example, the Kangqiao Development Zone of Nanhui
County will focus on building materials, while the Songjiang
County Development Zone will mainly develop the instrumental and
electrical appliance industries.
</P>
<P>
The suburban areas have become hot spots for foreign
investment. Some 30 top multinational companies have invested in
these nine zones which now cover a total of 15 sq. km.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, the development zones have attracted
nearly 1,000 projects, involving a total investment of 30 billion
yuan (3.61 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
In addition, local township enterprises in the suburbs will
increase their cooperation with large state-owned enterprises
and overseas business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
