<HEADLINE> Central China City Expands Export-Oriented Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The city of Huangshi in central
China's Hubei Province has seen increasing foreign investment in
its local economy, according to the city government.
</P>
<P>
A major raw material production center of gold, iron and steel
in China, Huangshi now has a total of 247 foreign-funded
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of last year, 36 overseas-funded companies
have been added, with overseas investment totalling 114 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Huangshi has led the province in exports from foreign-funded
enterprises, which totaled 155 million US dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Huangshi's foreign-funded enterprises had generated nearly 1.3
billion yuan in output value and more than 35 million yuan in
profits by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen foreign-funded enterprises have become
export-oriented. Improvement of investment environment and
services in is expected to give an impetus to the development of
Huangshi's export-led economy. 
</P>
