<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB to Host Meeting on Greater Mekong Subregion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
announced today that the Seventh Ministerial-level Conference on
Economic Cooperation in the Greater Mekong Subregion (GMS) will be
held in Manila on Thursday and Friday.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN), donor agencies and chambers of commerce and industry of
the GMS countries -- Cambodia, China, Laos, Myanmar, Thailand and
Vietnam, will attend the meeting, the Manila-based bank said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, to be hosted by the ADB, will be dominated by
discussions on resource mobilization, partnership and cooperation
between GMS governments and the business sector and donor
community, it said.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that about 100 subregional projects have been
identified by GMS countries, with the assistance of the ADB, for
priority implementation.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will review progress in implementing subregional
projects and seek financial support for and participation in the
projects by the donor community and the business sector, it said.
 
</P>
