<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> West China's Electricity to Be Transmitted to East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- West China's electricity will be
transmitted to ease electricity shortages in east China resulting
from its rapid economic development.
</P>
<P>
A project, under which hydropower and thermal electricity in
the central and western areas will be sent to the east through the
national grid, has been put into operation, according to the
Ministry of Power Industry.
</P>
<P>
The project also aims at linking the economically-developed
east to the underdeveloped west for mutual benefits, and improving
the uneven distribution of power resources.
</P>
<P>
Construction of a thermal power plant in north China's Shanxi
Province, a major coal producer, has started to support east
China's Jiangsu Province, one of the most developed areas in
China. The Three Gorges Hydropower Station is designed to transmit
7.2 million kw of electricity to east China, upon completion.
</P>
<P>
A second A.C. loop and D.C. hydropower project is well under
construction in southwest China's Guizhou Province to link with
Guangzhou. More projects of this kind will be put into operation
by the turn of the century, and three million kw of electricity
will be transmitted to east China.
</P>
<P>
Ninety percent of hydropower resources and 80 percent of coal
reserves in China are in the west and north, respectively, while
70 percent of China's energy is consumed by the east and central
areas.
</P>
<P>
And 94 percent of east China's generating capacity comes from
thermal power, and 75 percent of coal is shipped in from
north. This aggravates air pollution in the area. China's largest
industrial city of Shanghai now has difficulties in finding
suitable sites for construction of thermal power plants.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the program will greatly promote contacts and
cooperation between west and east. The west will for the first
time send its intensively-processed product of electricity instead
of raw materials, to the east. The east in turn will put more
investment, technology, and personnel into the west. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
