<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mushroom-Shape Moths Plague Bulgarian Forests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- A great number of highly
reproductive mushroom-shape moths have been found near eastern
Bulgaria's Varna region, putting the forests nearby in great
danger, Bulgarian Telegraph Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Forestry experts warned that the plague of mushroom-shape
moths, whose larvas have an exclusive appetite for leaves of
broadleaf trees, occur once about every 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, moth pests afflicted a few areas near Varna, while
up to 2,500 hectares of forests within 70 kilometers around the
city were endangered this year.
</P>
<P>
The pests will jeopardize orchards as well. Once entering the
orchards, the moths would eat up both leaves and flowers of fruit
trees.
</P>
<P>
So far, Bulgarian forestry authorities have taken emergency
measures and sprayed insecticide upon 97 percent of the country's
forests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970407.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Hospital Authority to Tighten Control on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Hospital Authority
has drawn up new guidelines against soliciting sponsorship and
donations from companies for doctors, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The authority, which manages 42 public hospitals and medical
institutes, is the territory's major drugs purchaser. Its
expenditure on 4,000 drugs and medicines has exceeded 1 billion HK
dollars (129 million US dollars) a year.
</P>
<P>
The guidelines which is expected to be issued next month mainly
target the pharmaceutical industry, which has very close links
with public doctors, as being the major sponsor for their academic
activities.
</P>
<P>
The Public Doctors' Association estimated that the amount of
drugs company sponsorship for doctors was about 20 million HK
dollars (2.58 million US dollars) a year.
</P>
<P>
Drugs companies have offered packages of "air fares, hotels and
conference fees" to doctors and the value of the sponsorship had
caused concern of the authority.
</P>
<P>
Hospital Authority deputy director Ko Wing-man said, "We want
to help doctors not to put themselves in a situation easily
suspected by others."
</P>
<P>
According to the guidelines, the employees of the Hospital
Authority must obtain written approval form their hospital or the
authority for sponsorship.
</P>
<P>
The authority should consider if the sponsorship could create
any obligation for the authority to the company, or if it could
adversely after the image of the authority.
</P>
<P>
Ko said that the authority had set up a special fund this month
to finance overseas courses or conferences for its 400-plus
consultants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
