<HEADLINE> Finland Wins Bronze in Ice Hockey Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Finland defeated China 3-0 and won
a fourth bronze medal at the World Women's Ice Hockey Championship
in Kitchener on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Finland's Paananen scored the opening goal on a power play at
13:27 of the third period.
</P>
<P>
Karoliina Raantamaki and Riikka Nieminen each added a goal in
the game's final five minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the tournament's closing game, Canada, seeking its fourth
gold medal, played the United States, the perpetual silver
medalist.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's first game, Sweden earned the fifth and final berth
for the 1998 Olympics by defeating Russia 3-1. Switzerland
defeated Norway 1-0 in the seeding game with a third-period goal
by Kathrin Lehmann.
</P>
<P>
Canada, the United States, Finland and China won Olympic berths
in preliminary play and, with Sweden, will be joined in Nagano by
Japan, the host country. It will be the first Olympics to include
women's ice hockey. 
</P>
