<HEADLINE> Bidding for Wanjiazhai Dam Project Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Bidding for earthwork of the
Wanjiazhai Dam Project on the Yellow River, the second longest
river in China, were opened here last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Eleven Sino-foreign joint ventures participated in the
bids. Foreign participants came from Austria, Japan, Germany,
France, and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The Wanjiazhai Project, named after a small village in Shanxi
Province, is to divert water from the Yellow River to
water-deficient Shanxi.
</P>
<P>
The Project will cost 12 billion yuan, which includes 400
million US dollars in loans from the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The first phase is to divert water to Taiyuan, the provincial
capital city, while the second phase to Shuozhou and Datong, two
major cities in Shanxi. The project will be completed in 2001.
</P>
</TEXT>
