<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Credit Cooperatives Involved in City Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong United Rural Credit
Cooperative, a syndicate of 28 local rural credit cooperatives,
will loan 1.2 billion yuan to projects in Pudong New Area, an
emerging trade and financial hub in Shanghai, this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Hongkui, president of the Pudong United Rural Credit
Cooperative, said that his company lent 170 million yuan to two
projects in Pudong this week.
</P>
<P>
"This is a good start for rural financial institutions to
extend loans to projects in Pudong," said Zhang Yaolun, deputy
director of the Administration Committee of the Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
Rural credit cooperatives are special banking institutions
widespread in the countryside, dealing with deposits and loans to
Chinese farmers.
</P>
<P>
The Pudong United Rural Credit Cooperative, which previously
belonged to the Agricultural Bank of China, but now became
independent, has self-managed funds of 670 million yuan. The
combination of loans and deposits of the cooperative reached 8.2
billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
The cooperative is preparing to set up a Shanghai Rural
Cooperative Bank, with other rural credit cooperatives in the
suburban counties of Shanghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
