<DOCNO> XIE19970407.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Background: ABCs of Basic Law of Hong Kong SAR (7-8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Following are the ABCs of the
Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (7-8) in
a question-and-answer format:
</P>
<P>
Question: Is it correct to say that the Basic Law is a
mini-constitution of the Hong Kong SAR?
</P>
<P>
Answer: The Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR is one of the basic
laws of China. It is not a constitution. Strictly speaking, it is
inaccurate to say the Basic Law is mini-constitution of the Hong
Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
This is because a constitution is the fundamental code of a
nation, whereas Hong Kong after 1997 is a special administrative
region of China. It is a local administrative region, not a
state. It is, therefore, improper to say the Basic Law is a
constitution or a mini-constitution.
</P>
<P>
In structure, however, the Basic Law does resemble a
constitution. It has a preamble, general principles, chapters and
sections on the basic rights and obligations of Hong Kong
residents, and Hong Kong's political structure, economy, culture
and education. Such a feature of the Basic Law is not found in
other domestic laws except the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
Perhaps due to this fact, or because of the importance of the
Basic Law in the legal system of the Hong Kong SAR, many people do
customarily refer to it as a mini-constitution.
</P>
<P>
Question: What is the relationship between the Basic Law and
laws to be enacted by the legislature of the Hong Kong SAR?
</P>
<P>
Answer: After 1997, laws in force in Hong Kong will include
the Basic Law, laws previously in force in Hong Kong which do not
contravene the Basic Law or which have been amended by the
legislature of the Hong Kong SAR (the common law, rules of equity,
ordinances, subordinate legislation and customary law), and laws
to be enacted by the legislature of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
These three groups of laws form the legal systems of the Hong
Kong SAR with the Basic Law as its core.
</P>
<P>
The NPC's decision on the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR
stipulates, "Systems, policies and laws to be instituted after
the establishment of the Hong Kong SAR shall be based on the Basic
Law of the Hong Kong SAR."
</P>
<P>
That is to say, after 1997, laws to be enacted by the
legislature of the Hong Kong SAR, previous laws to be enforced by
the Hong Kong SAR and policies of its government must be based on
the Basic Law and must not contravene it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970407.0200 </DOCNO>
