<HEADLINE> Tunisia Edges Namibia 2-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia snapped Namibia's
10-match home unbeaten streak with a 2-1 victory in a first-leg
World Cup qualifier soccer match in Windhoek, Namibia, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia jumped ahead as Taoufik Herichi scored after a corner
in the 15th minute.
</P>
<P>
Khared Badra beat the goalkeeper with a shot from 16 meters in
the 68th minute, putting Tunisia up by two goals.
</P>
<P>
Mahommed Auseb pulled one goal back with a power shot in the
75th minute. 
</P>
