<HEADLINE> Italy Sails into Davis Cup World Group Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Omar Camporese beat Albert
Costa Sunday to complete Italy's 4-1 defeat of Spain in a Davis
Cup World Group quarter-final in Pesaro, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Camporese beat Costa 6-2, 3-6, 6-4, after Carlos Moya downed
Italian Marzio Martelli 7-6 (7-5), 4-6, 6-3 to salvage a point for
Spain.
</P>
<P>
Italy virtually won the tie, played indoors on carpet, on
Saturday. Camporese combined with Diego Nargiso to beat Spain's
doubles team of Javier Sanchez and Francisco Roig 5-7, 7-6 (7-0),
6-2, 7-6 (7-5), giving the hosts an unbeatable 3-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Camporese paved the way to victory by shocking Moya, the
Australian Open finalist ranked eighth by the ATP Tour, in five
sets Friday. Furlan, ranked 64th, beat No. 12 Costa in Friday's
other singles match.
</P>
<P>
Italy, which lost to eventual champion France in last year's
semi-finals, takes on Sweden, which ousted South Africa 3-2
Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
