<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Pakistan 10-0 in 4-Nation Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese team today beat
Pakistan 10-0 in the four-nation Golden Jubilee International
Women field Hockey Tournament today at the National Stadium in
Pakistan's second largest city of Lahore.
</P>
<P>
In the second match Azerbaijan scored a narrow 1-0 win over
Singapore.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan,
Pakistan, considered underdogs, failed to match the superior
technique of their rivals and just once entered into the striking
circle of their rivals in the first half.
</P>
<P>
China, ranked fifth in the world and second in Asia, took a 4-0
lead at break.
</P>
<P>
Chinese skipper and ace striker Cai Xuemei struck four goals,
two in each half as home side struggled to counter their speedy
moves and aggressive attacks.
</P>
<P>
Superfit Chinese side forced two penalty corners in first five
minutes but failed to find net with indirect drills.
</P>
<P>
Chinese earned ten short corners and scored four goals out of
them after taking control right from beginning.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan which seemed a defensive force, launched a couple of
sitters in the last ten minutes of play but failed to break dead
lock as chinese defenders displayed brilliant clearance.
</P>
<P>
Chinese struck two field goals in space of two minutes to take
lead. Cai found the net with a scoop in the 11th minute and Gao
Min benefitted from a cross from Tang Chunling sent the ball in
left corner in the 12th minute.
</P>
<P>
Cai, brain behind attacks of chinese attacks, made it 3-0
after converting 9th penalty corner as Ma Xiaobing widened lead at
4-0 in a field attack from top of the circle in the 21st minute.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan lost the only sitter of half when right winger Samina
Naveed won the heart of crowd with a brilliant cross from the
right of circle but sluggish forwards failed to give it finishing
touch in the 17th minute.
</P>
<P>
Chinese went into second half with changed strategy of
engineering attacks from all available sources and jolted Pakistan
defence with a lovely display of cooperation among both flanks
plus mid field attacks.
</P>
<P>
Cai collected her third and teams fifth goal with superb shot
from top of the circle in the 39th minute as China added six goals
in ten minutes to struck their peak form and performance with a
rousing display of forceful sprints and collective efforts.
</P>
<P>
In a two players goal scoring sitter, chinese unmakred striker
Liu Lijie fed from a small gap pass from Li Congrong, just pushed
the ball in the left corner in the 43rd minute as Jain Miaoke
scored their seventh goal in field attack in the 45th minute.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan side trained by a Dutch coach for a couple of months,
conceded further humilation when Qu Bo netted a penalty stroke
goal in the 48th minute followed by penalty corner goal from Cai
in the coming minute.
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan and Singapore match failed to produce any sparkling
move and dazzling attack as both sides tested each other force
after confining the game to mid filed due to long time ball
possession.
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan missed their first short corner in the 14th minute
after strikers failed to stop the ball, showing lack of planning
and confidence out side the circle.
</P>
<P>
Singapore, a bunch of young players wasted their 17th minute
short corner with indirect attempt as Azerbaijan stamped their
supremacy with the second penalty corner in the 27th minute.
</P>
<P>
Vice captain and right winger Dmitriyenka's straight but
stinging shot sounded the boards after goalkeeper tried to save
with an acrobatic attempt from the left corner.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will meet Singapore and China will clash Azerbaijan
tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
