<HEADLINE> Angola Beats Togo 3-1 in World Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Angola came from one goal down to
beat Tongo 3-1 in a World Cup soccer qualifier here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The result lifted Angola to seven points in African qualifying
Group Four with a 2-1-0 record while Togo has yet to get a point.
</P>
<P>
Togo striker Byawole Djima stunned the Luanda crowd when he put
the visitors ahead after 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
But Angolan strikers Alves Antonio Paulao and Farbrice Akwa
turned the tables before the halftime, Paulao equalizing on the
half hour and Akwa converted a penalty kick after 44 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Sousa got the third goal six minutes into the second half.
</P>
